The Nigeria Governors’ Forum Secretariat, Abuja has started an induction program for newly-elected and returning governors. The programme is holding at the Banquet Hall of the Presidential Villa. In attendance are the newly-elected governors and the outgoing ones. President Muhammadu Buhari, who is in the United Kingdom on a “private visit,” is being represented at the event by his deputy, Professor Yemi Osinbajo (SAN). Chairman of the Forum and the outgoing Governor of Zamafara State, Abdulaziz Yari, told the newly-elected governors to get ready to face new challenges.